> The original Jenny Lind Singers were founded in 1970 at Malvern Girls' =
College by their Head of Music, Eric Hemery, together with Elaine =
Hugh-Jones, a well-known local composer and teacher of music at MGC. =
Pieces were sung by that group on a record made by MGC in 1973, but they =
later ceased to exist.
> In 2013, at the invitation of the Malvern Civic Society, the Jenny =
Lind Singers were re-founded by Lynne Lindner, then the Director of =
Music at Malvern St James Girls=E2=80=99 School, and initially comprised =
singers whom Lynne had taught, some of whom were still at the school, =
while others had gone on to Music Colleges or University.
>=20
> The group now comprises local adult female singers, many of them =
professional or semi-professional musicians, and with the continued =
participation in some concerts, notably the group=E2=80=99s Christmas =
concerts, of trained singers who are past pupils of Lynne=E2=80=99s.
>=20
> The JLS are delighted to have as their patron Countess Dr Inga =
Lewenhaupt, former Chair of the Jenny Lind Society of Sweden.
>=20
> Their regular accompanist is local professional pianist Tim Sidford, =
and they have also been accompanied by harpists Nia Evans and Anwen Mai =
Thomas.
>=20
